---
id: org.dxos.plugin.video
name: VideoPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A plugin for `DXOS` Composer that stores videos and transcribes them via a
remote `EDGE` transcription service.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`     |

## Types

```mdl
type Text
  desc: Plain/markdown text object from `@dxos/schema`. Referenced, not defined here.
```

```mdl
type Video
  desc: A video resource with optional linked transcript and summary.
  fields:
    name: string              # label
    url: string               # source URL; embeddable in an iframe
    transcript?: Ref<Text>    # optional link to a generated transcript text object
    summary?: Ref<Text>       # optional link to a generated summary text object
```

## Components

```mdl
component VideoArticle
  desc: Article surface that plays a Video and offers transcription.
  props:
    video: Video
  state:
    transcribing: boolean       # transcription request in flight
    summarizing: boolean        # summarization request in flight
    view: transcript | summary  # which text the tabbed editor shows
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode
  actions:
    transcribe()                # invokes op:transcribeVideo
    summarize()                 # invokes op:summarizeVideo
    openOriginal()              # opens video.url in a new tab
  emits:
    onTranscribed(transcript: Ref<Text>)
    onSummarized(summary: Ref<Text>)
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────────────────┐
    │ [toolbar slot] Transcribe│
    ├──────────────────────────┤
    │                          │
    │   <iframe> video embed   │
    │                          │
    ├──────────────────────────┤
    │ transcript link (if any) │
    └──────────────────────────┘
```

## Services

```mdl
service TranscriptionService
  desc: Remote EDGE worker that transcribes a video URL to text.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    transcribe(url: string, lang: string) → Text
  note: |
    HTTP GET https://transcription.dxos.network/video?url=<url>&lang=<lang>
    Response: { success: boolean, result: { videoId, title, languageCode, generated, text } }.
    lang defaults to "en". The worker sends no CORS headers, so the browser request is routed
    through the EDGE CORS proxy via `proxyFetchLegacy` from @dxos/edge-client.
  errors:
    TranscriptionFailed: worker returned a non-2xx response, success=false, or empty text
```

## Operations

```mdl
op transcribeVideo
  desc: |
    Transcribes a Video via the EDGE TranscriptionService, creates a Text
    object with the result, and links it back via Video.transcript.
  input:
    video: Ref<Video>
    lang?: string               # defaults to "en"
  output: Ref<Text>             # the created/linked transcript
  errors:
    TranscriptionFailed: EDGE worker did not return a transcript
    VideoNotFound: video ref could not be resolved
  effects: [http, echo:write, echo:read]
  requires: [TranscriptionService]
  note: |
    Resolves video.url → GET worker → Text.make({ content }) →
    Database write → Obj.update(video, { transcript: Ref.make(text) }).
    Also adopts the worker's `result.title` as Video.name when the name is empty.
    Exposed on the ./operations subpath for blueprint/tool reuse.
```

```mdl
op summarizeVideo
  desc: |
    Summarizes a Video's transcript via the assistant AI stack, creates a Text object with the
    markdown summary, and links it back via Video.summary.
  input:
    video: Ref<Video>
  output: Ref<Text>             # the created/linked summary
  errors:
    NoTranscript: video has no transcript to summarize
    SummarizationFailed: the AI request produced no summary
  effects: [ai, echo:write, echo:read]
  requires: [Database.Service, AiService]
  note: |
    Loads video.transcript content → AiRequest.run with a summarization system prompt
    (claude-sonnet) → Text.make({ content }) → Database write →
    Obj.update(video, { summary: Ref.make(text) }). Requires AI/BYOK configured in the host.
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Store Video

  req F-1.1: A Video is created with a name and url.
  req F-1.2: Video.transcript is initially unset.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Play Video

  req F-2.1:
    when: a Video is opened in the article surface
    then: the video is rendered in an embed iframe derived from Video.url

  req F-2.2:
    when: Video.url cannot be embedded
    then: a fallback link to the url is shown
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Transcribe Video

  req F-3.1:
    when: the user triggers Transcribe on the VideoArticle
    then: op:transcribeVideo is invoked with the Video ref and lang

  req F-3.2:
    when: op:transcribeVideo runs
    then: TranscriptionService.transcribe is called with Video.url and lang
    errors: [TranscriptionFailed]

  req F-3.3:
    when: the service returns transcript text
    then: a Text object is created and Video.transcript is set to reference it

  req F-3.4:
    when: a request is in flight
    then: VideoArticle reflects a transcribing state and disables re-triggering
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Summarize Video

  req F-4.1:
    when: the user triggers Summarize on the VideoArticle
    then: op:summarizeVideo is invoked with the Video ref
    note: the action is enabled only once Video.transcript exists

  req F-4.2:
    when: op:summarizeVideo runs
    then: the transcript content is summarized via the AI stack
    errors: [NoTranscript, SummarizationFailed]

  req F-4.3:
    when: the AI returns a summary
    then: a Text object is created and Video.summary is set to reference it
```

```mdl
feat F-5: View Transcript and Summary

  req F-5.1:
    when: Video.transcript or Video.summary is set
    then: VideoArticle shows a Transcript/Summary tab strip below the player

  req F-5.2:
    when: a tab is selected
    then: the editor renders that text object read-only (markdown), live-bound to ECHO

  req F-5.3:
    when: op:summarizeVideo completes
    then: the view switches to the Summary tab
    tags: [follow-up: comments anchored to the summary via the comments plugin]
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Create video
  given: a new Video is created with name and url
  then:
    - Video.name and Video.url are set
    - Video.transcript is unset
```

```mdl
test T-2: Render embed player
  given: a Video with an embeddable url is opened in the article surface
  then: an iframe with the derived embed src is rendered
```

```mdl
test T-3: Transcribe success
  given: a Video with a url, EDGE worker returns { text }
  when: op:transcribeVideo is invoked
  then:
    - TranscriptionService.transcribe called with the url and lang
    - a Text object is created with the returned text
    - Video.transcript references the created Text
    - the transcript Ref is returned
```

```mdl
test T-4: Transcribe failure leaves video unchanged
  given: a Video with a url, EDGE worker returns a non-2xx response
  when: op:transcribeVideo is invoked
  then:
    - TranscriptionFailed error returned
    - no Text object created
    - Video.transcript remains unset
```

```mdl
test T-5: Open transcript
  given: a Video whose transcript is set, opened in the article surface
  then: an affordance to open the transcript target is shown
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document are defined below using
the core `ext` primitive — the only construct the base language provides.

```mdl
ext type
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap        # name[?]: TypeExpr  (# inline comment)
    literals?: UnionList     # a | b | c
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self              # feat blocks may contain feat blocks
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap            # external inputs (immutable inside component)
    state?: FieldMap            # internal reactive state
    slots?: FieldMap            # named ReactNode injection points
    actions?: ActionMap         # methods the component exposes or handles
    emits?: EventMap            # events the component raises to its parent
    layout?: CodeBlock          # ASCII sketch of visual structure (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: |
    A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
    Pure ops have no effects or requires. Effectful ops declare both.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap            # named input parameters
    output?: TypeExpr           # return type
    errors?: ErrorMap           # name: Prose  (when this error occurs)
    effects?: EffectList        # echo:read | echo:write | http | fs | ...
    requires?: ServiceList      # injected service dependencies
    note?: Prose                # implementation guidance (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext service
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0
  desc: An external or system-level dependency providing named operations.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    loading?: eager | lazy
    ops?: OpMap                 # name(params) → ReturnType
    errors?: ErrorMap
    note?: Prose
```
